TITLE: Starting and joining a background thread to spin ROS 2 executor in main() function in Python
DESCRIPTION: Shows adding a new thread in main() to call spin_in_background(), starting it after rclpy.init(), and joining the thread before exiting to keep the ROS 2 callbacks running in background during execution.
