TITLE: Handling asynchronous goal response and result retrieval
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to asynchronously handle the goal response callback, check for rejection, and if accepted, request and process the final result using futures and callbacks, enabling efficient asynchronous goal and result management in ROS 2 actions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ros2/ros2_documentation/blob/rolling/source/Tutorials/Intermediate/Writing-an-Action-Server-Client/Py.rst#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
def goal_response_callback(future):
    goal_handle = future.result()
    if not goal_handle.accepted:
        print('Goal rejected')
        return
    result_future = goal_handle.get_result_async()
    result_future.add_done_callback(result_callback)

def result_callback(future):
    result = future.result().result
    print('Result:', result.sequence)
```

