TITLE: Declaring a Custom Memory Resource Class Using std::pmr in C++
DESCRIPTION: Defines a skeleton for a custom memory resource class by deriving from std::pmr::memory_resource. This class declares the required override functions: do_allocate for allocating memory with a specified byte size and alignment, do_deallocate for freeing memory with the same parameters, and do_is_equal to compare memory resource equality. Dependencies include the C++17 <memory_resource> header. The snippet serves as a base for building a real-time friendly allocator compatible with the ROS 2 allocator interface.
