TITLE: Node Interface Code Example (C++)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides the key parts of the rclcpp::NodeInterfaces example. It defines the `MyNodeInterfaces` type and the `node_info` function that takes this interface as an argument, using the `NodeBaseInterface` and `NodeLoggingInterface` to access and display the node's name, demonstrating how to define and use `NodeInterfaces<>`. It also highlights how to use this approach to simplify the code.
