TITLE: Creating a Service Client in ROS 1 and ROS 2
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to create and use a service client in both ROS 1 and ROS 2.  The ROS 2 version creates a service client using `node.create_client()`, waits for service availability, and then calls the service asynchronously using `call_async()`.  The example also notes the restriction on `rclpy.spin_until_future_complete` usage within ROS 2 callbacks.
